# Changelog Maintenance

Whenever you add, modify, or delete a file in `backend/`, `frontend/`, `tests/`, `knowledge_base/`, or the project root (e.g. `requirements.txt`, `.env.example`), you **must** update `ai/changelog.md`.

## Format

Add a new entry at the top of the file (below the intro paragraph, above the previous top entry):

```markdown
## [Patch] – YYYY-MM-DD · Short title
_No commit yet_ (or **Commit:** `abc1234` if committed)

### Added / Changed / Removed
- `path/to/file.py` – One-line description of what changed and why
```

## Rules

- Use `### Added` for new files, `### Changed` for edits, `### Removed` for deletions
- One bullet per file changed — be specific about what was modified, not just that it was touched
- Always use today's date
- If a phase commit is being made, replace `_No commit yet_` with the commit hash after committing
- Do not batch unrelated changes into one entry — use separate entries if changes serve different purposes
